50|$|The Swiss <b>civil</b> <b>code</b> is {{considered}} mainly {{influenced by the}} German <b>civil</b> <b>code</b> and partly influenced by the French <b>civil</b> <b>code.</b> The <b>civil</b> <b>code</b> of the Republic of Turkey is a slightly {{modified version of the}} Swiss code, adopted in 1926 during Mustafa Kemal Atatürk's presidency as part of the government's progressive reforms and secularization.|$|R
